    "Dimension reduction is crucial in machine learning for simplifying complex data sets (Van Der Maaten et al. 2009), reducing computational complexity (Ray et al. 2021), and mitigating the curse of dimensionality (Talpur et al. 2023), ultimately improving model performance and interpretability.",
    "Dimension reduction encompasses two primary approaches: feature selection (Solorio-Fernández et al. 2022), which involves choosing a subset of the most informative features from the original data-set to reduce dimensionality while maintaining interpretability; and feature extraction (Li et al. 2022), a method where new, lower-dimensional features are derived from the original data to capture essential patterns and relationships."
